gs":[{"name":"Talbot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Marcel, Anatole, Armand, Aubert, Camille, Gilles, Normand, Adrien, Alcide, Andre, Auguste.","English and Irish (of Norman origin); French: from the Anglo-Norman French personal name <i>Talebot</i>, a pet form of Old French <i>Talebert</i>, <i>Talbert</i> (see   Talbert   1). Compare   Talbert   2.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Talbald</i>, composed of the elements <i>dal</i> ‘bright, proud’ or <i>tal</i> ‘valley’ + <i>bald</i> ‘bold’."],"variants":[{"name":"Talbert","meanings":["English and Scottish (of Norman origin); French: from the Old French personal name <i>Talebert</i>, <i>Talbert</i>, from ancient Germanic <i>Talaberht</i> or <i>Dalbert</i>, composed of the elements <i>dal</i> ‘bright, proud’ or <i>tal</i> ‘valley’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright’.","Altered form of English   Talbot  , a cognate of 1 above."]},{"name":"Talbott","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Talbot  ."]}]},{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen Talbot was born in 1458, in England. She had at least 1 son with Sir William Singleton. She died in 1507, at the age of 49."},"et":{"1458–1507":"1458–1507","1455–1530":"1455–1530","1457–1488":"1457–1488","1479–1532":"1479–1532","1486–1551":"1486–1551","1480–1551":"1480–1551","about 1480":"umbes 1486","1480":"1480","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1457":"1457","1488":"1488","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","about 1479":"umbes 1479","1486":"1486","1530":"1530","1551":"1551","1507":"1507","Coddington, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Coddington, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1458–1507":"1458–1507","1455–1530":"1455–1530","1457–1488":"1457–1488","1479–1532":"1479–1532","1486–1551":"1486–1551","1480–1551":"1480–1551","about 1480":"noin 1486","1480":"1480","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1457":"1457","1488":"1488","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","about 1479":"noin 1479","1486":"1486","1530":"1530","1551":"1551","1507":"1507","Coddington, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Coddington, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1458–1507":"1458–1507","1455–1530":"1455–1530","1457–1488":"1457–1488","1479–1532":"1479–1532","1486–1551":"1486–1551","1480–1551":"1480–1551","about 1480":"environ 1486","1480":"1480","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1457":"1457","1488":"1488","1532":"1532","1455":"1455","about 1479":"environ 1479","1486":"1486","1530":"1530","1551":"1551","1507":"1507","Coddington, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Coddington, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Ellen Talbot est née en 1458, à Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils 